issue.title: Currying support
issue.body: The current code generator does not support currying: it verifies that the supplies arguments to a function match the given patterns of a function. The code generator should check that the supplied arguments are at most equal in count to the patterns, and in case of an incomplete call, produce the curried function, of less argument.

issue.title: FFI is not integrated with equation-matching system or method resolver
Pattern match failures of functions called from another function body bubble up
issue.body: Suppose a function `A` calls a function `B` in its definition, but the call to `B` fails due to a pattern match failure. The `PatternMatchError` coming from `B` will bubble up to the `dispatchEquation` that called `A`'s implementation, and will cause the next equation for `A` to be tried. This is not desired behaviour.
